sentence: On  Oct.  7,  Hamas-led  militants  stormed  from  the  Gaza  Strip  into  Israel,  killed  1,400  people  and  took  more  than  240  hostages,  according  to  Israeli  officials.

In  response,  Israel's  military  has  launched  near-continuous  airstrikes  on  the  Gaza  Strip,  killing  over  10,000  Palestinians,  according  to  Gaza's  Health  Ministry,  and  displacing  nearly  1.
Israel  has  said  the  attacks  killed  dozens  of  militants,  including  Hamas  commanders.
The  Health  Ministry  in  Gaza  said  at  least  195  people  were  killed.
On  Friday,  Israel  struck  an  ambulance  convoy  at  Gaza's  largest  medical  facility,  Al-Shifa  Hospital,  killing  at  least  13,  according  to  the  World  Health  Organization.
Late  on  Saturday,  bombs  fell  on  Al-Maghazi  refugee  camp,  killing  at  least  45,  according  to  Gaza's  Health  Ministry.
Nearby,  The  Associated  Press  reports  that  Israeli  airstrikes  struck  near  Bureij  refugee  camp,  killing  at  least  13.
